        <name>6.2.2.2 cosh^2-sinh^2</name>
        <questiontext>&lt;p class="HELM_exercise"&gt;Exercise&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We derive a fundamental identity relating hyperbolic functions&amp;nbsp;&lt;span class="math inline"&gt;\(\cosh^2x-\sinh^2x \equiv \ ?\)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ol class="HELM_parts"&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;p&gt; First, express \(\cosh^2x\) in terms of the exponential functions. Expand your answer.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;\(\cosh^2x \equiv \) [[input:ans1]] [[validation:ans1]] [[feedback:prt1]]&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;p&gt; Similarly, express \(\sinh^2x\) in terms of the exponential functions. Expand your answer.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;\(\sinh^2x \equiv \) [[input:ans2]] [[validation:ans2]] [[feedback:prt2]]&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;p&gt; Finally determine &lt;span class="math inline"&gt;\(\cosh^2x-\sinh^2x\)&lt;/span&gt; using the results from (a) and (b):&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;\(\cosh^2x-\sinh^2x \equiv \) [[input:ans3]] [[validation:ans3]] [[feedback:prt3]]&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Alternatively, we can prove the above identity by using the relations \(e^x \equiv \cosh x + \sinh x\) and \(e^{-x} \equiv \cosh x - \sinh x .\)
&lt;p&gt;See solution/feedback if you cannot work this out on your own.&lt;/p&gt;</questiontext>
        <questiontextformat>1</questiontextformat>
        <generalfeedback>&lt;p&gt;Here is a step by step calculation.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;\[ \begin{align*} \cosh^2x &amp;amp; \equiv \left( {@cosh@} \right)^2 \equiv \frac{1}{4}(e^x+e^{-x})^2 \\ &amp;amp; \equiv \frac{1}{4}[(e^x)^2+2e^xe^{-x}+(e^{-x})^2] \equiv \frac{1}{4}[e^{2x}+2e^{x-x}+e^{-2x}] \\ &amp;amp; \equiv {@cosh2@} .\end{align*} \]&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;\[ \begin{align*} \sinh^2x\ &amp;amp; \equiv \left( {@sinh@} \right)^2 \equiv \frac{1}{4}(e^x-e^{-x})^2 \\ &amp;amp; \equiv \frac{1}{4}[(e^x)^2-2e^xe^{-x}+(e^{-x})^2] \equiv \frac{1}{4}[e^{2x}-2e^{x-x}+e^{-2x}] \\ &amp;amp; \equiv&amp;nbsp; {@sinh2@}. \end{align*} \]&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Alternatively, using \(e^x \equiv \cosh x + \sinh x\) and \(e^{-x} \equiv \cosh x - \sinh x \), we obtain \[1 \equiv e^x \cdot e^{-x} \equiv (\cosh x + \sinh x)(\cosh x - \sinh x) \equiv \cosh^2x - \sinh^2x \] as desired.&lt;/p&gt;</generalfeedback>
